The paper proposes a novel approach for unsupervised structure learning in high-dimensional time series data using a combination of recurrent neural networks and state space models. This approach has applications in behavior understanding, medical diagnosis, speech modeling, and sequential multi-objects recognition. Given the focus on neural networks and machine learning, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
